    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="470" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d470">
                <head>Argyle Square Junior Members Society</head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Argyle Square Junior Members’ Society</hi>, <lb/> 24
                            <hi rend="italic">Grafton Place, Euston Square,
                                <placeName>London</placeName>
                    </hi>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-06">
                        <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 6, 1865</date>.</dateline>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I beg to hand you a copy of a resolution
                        passed at a general meeting of this society, held last evening, expressing
                        condolence with the American nation on the late disastrous assassination of
                        Mr. Lincoln.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be your excellency’s most obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>H. FRANCIS MORSE, </signed>
                    <hi rend="italic">Hon. Sec</hi>.</closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps"> C. F. Adams</hi>.</p>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="italic">Resolved</hi>, That this meeting desires to give
                            utterence to the feelings of grief With which it has heard of the
                            assassination of President Lincoln, and to convey to Mrs. Lincoln, and
                            to the United States government and people, an expresssion of their
                            deepest sympathy and condolence.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
